12.short_description: Decentralizing rapid testing across industries

18.description:
Unima is decentralizing rapid testing across industries by taking diagnostics out of the lab to the place these are needed the most to secure a timely diagnostic for everyone, anywhere.

Unima is solving is the centralization of lab testing, which limits the access to a timely diagnostic for billions. Current technology for diagnostics is very precise and can detect almost any disease known, but the problem is these require labs with expensive equipment and specialized technicians making lab testing impossible to scale up to provide universal and timely access to diagnostics.

To solve this problem Unima developed Find, a rapid testing technology platform for real time diagnostics which allows anyone to diagnose a disease directly where it is needed, without using lab equipment, with results in 15 minutes or less and at a very low cost. With Find anyone can have access to a timely diagnostic even in the most remote areas of the world.

The Find platform uses shark antibodies modified with genetic engineering to detect disease biomarkers in blood, saliva, urine or water samples. These shark antibodies are used in microfluidic cards and generate a visual reactions when in contact with specific biomarkers of the disease to be tested. Then to evaluate the result of the test, a picture of the testing card is taken with the proprietary Xplora smartphone app which runs image analysis process and neural network algorithms to generate an inmediate result. Then this result,along with contextual information like geolocation, date and time, is sent to a cloud server where it can be used for real time disease tracking.

12.short_description: Crowd-lending platform for residential and commercial solar systems

18.description:
Red Girasol Crowdfunding platform for residential and commercial solar systems in Mexico. It connects people who wish to acquire a panel system with investors willing to contribute money until they complete the amount they need to pay for it in exchange for immediate returns. For their part, residents get the benefit of paying month to month at interest rates lower than those offered by other companies in the market.

The company, through an algorithm, first analyzes the light receipt that the user shares and, based on this, presents a quotation plan with different installers in agreement with Girasol. By choosing the one that best suits your needs, the resident must provide at least 10% of the total price. Then start the funding campaign and once the goal is completed, the installation happens.

From there, the company charges the user's credit card the payment of the monthly payment to investors, whose interest and yield are assigned to both depending on the hitch and term selected in the case of the first and the amount contributed in the case of the second. Girasol obtains profits by charging commissions to the three actors in its network (residents, investors and suppliers).

The company started its operation in 2016 in Monterrey, Nuevo León.

12.short_description: Legally secured contracts on the Blockchain

18.description:
Mifiel is the most trusted e-signature SaaS solution in Mexico. The platform has been entrusted to secure legal documents of hundreds of organizations including multinational banks and Fortune 500 companies.

The advanced e-signatures* generated by Mifiel are presumed to be authentic in court unless the signer can prove otherwise, giving it advantage over any other e-signature standard or even autograph signatures. As such, Mifiel provides a more legally robust alternative to widely used e-signature platforms that are better suited to the legal systems in the U.S. and the U.K.

Mifiel is also the first platform in the world to enable the secure electronic transfer of endorsable documents (e.g. negotiable instruments such as promissory notes, titles, etc.) by leveraging blockchain technology.


*An advanced e-signature is akin to a digital identification card issued by the government, often associated to the biometric data of the individual to which it belongs. It is composed of a cryptographic key pair (provided as files or as files embedded within a chip in an ID card) that allows the individual to securely authenticate their identity and sign documents digitally. There are over 60 countries in the world that emit such signatures, most notably in Mexico, the EU, and East Asia.
